    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the sausage meat is cooked, add the <strong>halved tomatoes </strong>and <strong>fennel seeds </strong>(not a fan of aniseed? Only add a little!) to the pan with your <strong>dried oregano</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until the tomatoes have begun to break down</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>and <strong>tomato paste </strong>in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[225ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p>",
